<BYLINE>By JEFF WILSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> returns to his beloved <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> as the toast of <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>, reinvigorating the social scene with the stature of a popular two-term president who never forgot his show business past. <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> and <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> do n't hide their eagerness to step out of the national spotlight and re-enter a private world among friends. The president has said: `` Every time I come home I say to myself, ` Why did I ever leave?''' Their affluent friends are no less eager. `` It's tough to beat a former president living in your midst. They are now going to be the superstars in the <LOCATION> Bel-Air </LOCATION> circuit,'' entertainment industry observer <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Archerd </ORGANIZATION> said. `` Hollywood feels it sent one of its own to the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> and now he's returned as the most popular president in history. He's one of us,'' said TV producer <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> <PERSON> Willenborg </PERSON>. <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON> and <PERSON> Barron </PERSON> <PERSON> Hilton </PERSON> set the social tone by throwing a $ 25,000-a-table homecoming gala earlier this month. The <ORGANIZATION> Reagans </ORGANIZATION> will be a star attraction Feb. 23 at the <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Hope Award presentations honoring <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON> and a Valentine's Day party is on tap for Mrs. `` They will really re-invigorate things,'' dance man <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> predicted. <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON> said the social calendar is already topsy-turvy. `` I'm sure they will be the leaders of everything that happens here,'' he said. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> never forgot <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>, where he starred in motion pictures and led the <ORGANIZATION> Scr