<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VERSAILLES, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Ah, soon the pitter-patter of little feet _ lots of them _ might be heard at the White House. <PERSON> Millie </PERSON>, President-elect and <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s springer spaniel, has spent the last two weeks at a farm in <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION>, where she was mated with Tug, a springer spaniel owned by Will and <PERSON> Sarah </PERSON> <PERSON> Farish </PERSON>. `` We believe she's pregnant, but we do n't know that for a fact,'' <PERSON> Farish </PERSON> said Monday. <PERSON> Farish </PERSON> said they would know in about three weeks if the 2-year-old dog is pregnant. If she is, she likely would give birth in March. The Farishes gave <PERSON> Millie </PERSON> to the Bushes about a year ago. <PERSON> Farish </PERSON> said he telephoned Mrs. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> on Friday and `` told her everything had gone fine.'' `` She's very close to <PERSON> Millie </PERSON>,'' he said.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>PITTSFIELD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A retired obstetrician used his trade skills and techniques he saw on a television show about a veterinarian to `` deliver'' a 55-pound dog from the 6-foot deep hole it had been digging for months. Dr. <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Dorman </PERSON>'s next-door neighbor called him Saturday night when she found <PERSON> Dusty </PERSON>, a 10-year-old mutt, was stuck in the hole, with just his wagging tail sticking out. <PERSON> Dorman </PERSON> got a shovel and pickax, but found they were of limited use on the frozen ground. Drawing on his experience delivering breech babies and memories of the TV show `` All Creatures Great and Small,'' <PERSON> Dorman </PERSON> worked his arm into the hole, grabbed the dog's hind legs, stretched them out and tied them with a rope. He then pulled the rope slowly to free the mutt, which was dirty but unharmed. `` This was the first delivery I've had since I stopped practicing seven years ago,'' <PERSON> Dorman </PERSON> said. `` I hope it's my last breech delivery.''
