<DATELINE>MANCHESTER, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police broke into a church early today and dragged away a Sri Lankan who had taken refuge there and was sleeping handcuffed to a radiator, his supporters said. Home Office Minister <PERSON> Timothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Renton </PERSON> said <PERSON> Viraj </PERSON> <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON>, 32, would be sent back to <LOCATION> Sri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lanka </LOCATION> if he did not find another country to accept him by Friday. <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON> says he faces persecution and possible death in his native country because of his communist beliefs and support for the Tamil minority. The British government and courts disagree. The Rev. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Methuen </PERSON> of the Church of the Ascension said police arrived at his home about 7:30 a.m. and broke down the door leading to the vestry where <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON> was staying with two supporters. <PERSON> Methuen </PERSON> said there was `` quite a lot'' of damage done to the building. A Home Office spokesman confirmed that two immigration officers and 50 police officers forced their way into the Church of <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> premises in northern <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>. `` The door into the sacristy -LRB- or vestry -RRB- was a large wooden door which was heavily bolted and barred,'' said <PERSON> Terry </PERSON> <PERSON> Platt </PERSON>, head of the Immigration and Nationality section at the Home Office. `` They forced that door with special equipment which had the result of doing some damage to the door and wall.'' <PERSON> Ingrid </PERSON> <PERSON> Falat </PERSON>, a member of the church council, said <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON> was `` handcuffed to the radiator in the room ... they dragged him out by his hands and feet.'' Falat and other witnesses said the police used acetylene torches to remove the handcuffs. <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON> has lost two immigration appeals, a High Court judicial review and a <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANI