rom 1952 until 1985 and was re-elected in October. As Public Works alderman in <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION>, he razed several old neighborhoods to make way for high-rise buildings, and <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION> became known for its destructive urban renewal. The brigade letter named a <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION> construction company as one of <PERSON> Vanden </PERSON> <PERSON> Boeynants </PERSON>' business partners who must help contribute funds to the ransom
