<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 It costs a pretty penny to ride in style around the nation's capital this inaugural week, and even wealthy would-be power travelers may find themselves hailing taxicabs if they procrastinate. Limousine operators report capacity or near-capacity bookings for the week. One has switched its phones over to an answering service, whose operators deliver the news: `` They are booked solid.'' Those fortunate enough to find a limousine are paying to keep it at their disposal. Because of demand, most Washington-area companies are leasing on a three - or four-day basis, with the car and chauffeur on call eight to 10 hours each day The cost: $ 2,700 at <ORGANIZATION> Presidential </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Limousine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>. There is an alternative package, referred to among the in-crowd as `` sans stretch.'' Translation: For $ 1,600 one can rent a car and driver for four days, but the car will be a <ORGANIZATION> Lincoln </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Town </ORGANIZATION> Car sedan, not the stretch limousine that comes with the pricier deal. Some companies are charging more; some a bit less. `` It's really a seller's market,'' said Presidential's <PERSON> Herta </PERSON> <PERSON> Mullens </PERSON>. Some would-be clients have special requests. `` A lot have asked for bodyguards,'' said <PERSON> Mullens </PERSON>. `` We call it executive protection, but they're essentially bodyguards.'' High rollers who do n't need a limo for four days but want a classy ride to a single event may find it tough to find one. But, not surprisingly, where there's a wallet, there's a way. `` If they are willing to pay the price, no one will go home unhappy,'' <PERSON> Mullens </PERSON> said. `` With a little shuffling I can get someone from their hotel to a ball for $ 1,000.'' The ball-bound appear undeterred by the cost. `` They pause for a while when they hear the price,'' said <PERSON> Mullens </PERSON>, `` and then say ` OK, put me down.'''
