<HEAD>Sri Lankan Forcibly Taken Away After Two Years In Church</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANCHESTER, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police burst into a church vestry Wednesday and dragged away a Sri Lankan seeking political asylum, an action one critic called an `` act of savagery'' against the ancient right to sanctuary. <PERSON> Viraj </PERSON> <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON>, an activist who says he fears persecution or death if he returns home, had handcuffed himself to a radiator when 16 police and two immigration agents broke into the Church of the Ascension in the rundown <PERSON> Hulme </PERSON> district, police said. Police cut <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON>' handcuffs with acetylene torches, and a witness said the 32-year-old screamed `` Murderers! Murderers!'' as they took him to a <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> prison to await deportation, scheduled for Friday. Officials said <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON>, who had been living in the church since receiving a deportation order two years ago, would be sent home unless a third country accepted him. `` The fact that someone is in a church does not give them any immunity from the law,'' Home Secretary <PERSON> Douglas </PERSON> <PERSON> Hurd </PERSON> told a noisy session of <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION>. Some opposition lawmakers shouted `` Sieg heil!'' and `` KGB!'' Three spectators, one shouting `` Do not send him to his death!'' were thrown out of the public gallery. But other politicians cheered as <PERSON> Hurd </PERSON>, the minister responsible for immigration affairs, warned the church to `` think carefully before it enters into any habit or custom of giving shelter to those defying the law.'' Home Office Minister <PERSON> Timothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Renton </PERSON> said the government `` always felt that the situation in <LOCATION> Sri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lanka </LOCATION> did not justify the position that <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON> and his supporters were adopting.'' <PERSON> Mendis </PERSON>, a member of his nation's Sinhalese majority, says his life is threatened by his political activism on behalf of communism and the Tamil mi