<HEAD>GAO Says Pentagon Has Ambitious Schedule for Rail Garrison System</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DONNA CASSATA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> has an ambitious schedule for developing a rail garrison system for the MX missile, according to a congressional agency report that says there could be cost and performance problems if the program is not closely supervised. The <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Accounting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION>, an investigating arm of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, said in a report this week that the department's acquisition strategy for the rail garrison system calls for the start of production two years before development contracts have been completed. This overlap between production and development, known as concurrency, must be `` well planned and controlled,'' the <ORGANIZATION> GAO </ORGANIZATION> said, otherwise, `` it can cause cost, schedule and performance problems, as demonstrated in other <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> acquisition programs.'' In addition, the <ORGANIZATION> GAO </ORGANIZATION> said that by March 1990, when the department must make an initial production decision on the rail garrison, only about two years of the system's planned four-year test program will have been completed. `` Most systems integration testing, all basing verification missile flight tests, and most of the operational test and evaluation effort will remain to be done,'' said the <ORGANIZATION> GAO </ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>, in comments included in the <ORGANIZATION> GAO </ORGANIZATION> report, concurred with all of the agency's findings. It added that the department believes the system of launching missiles from the rails is similar to silo launches and does not require special tests. Under the rail garrison system, 50 missiles would be placed on 25 trains that would be parked inside train alert shelters in garrisons at <ORGANIZ