<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Combustion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Engineering </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and Paris-based <ORGANIZATION> Alsthom </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SA </ORGANIZATION> announced plans Wednesday to combine their steam-boiler businesses in a joint venture that would have combined revenues of about $ 2 billion. Combustion Engineering and <ORGANIZATION> Alsthom </ORGANIZATION> would own roughly equal shares in the joint venture, which is subject to approval by each company's board of directors and regulatory agencies in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> and the European Common Market Talks leading to a definitive agreement are expected to take several months, the companies said in a joint statement. The fossil-fueled steam boilers are used by electric utilities and industrial users for generating power. `` Alsthom has been a licensee of C-E's steam generating technology for 40 years and is an important supplier in the European community and elsewhere,'' <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hugel </PERSON>, Combustion's chairman and chief executive, said in a statement. `` We have great respect for their capability.'' <ORGANIZATION> Alsthom </ORGANIZATION> said its equity in the venture will be transferred to a new joint venture company recently announced with <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>. Combustion Engineering, which had net income of $ 56.6 million on sales of $ 3 billion in 1987, provides engineering products, services and systems to power-generating customers worldwide. Alsthom, which had sales of $ 4.7 billion in 1987, is a leading manufacturer of industrial products and services concentrated in energy, mass transportation and ship building, and a leading supplier of