<HEAD>Quarterly, Annual Profits Up 13 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Westinghouse </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday its fourth-quarter and 1988 annual profits each rose 13 percent on revenue gains of more than 10 percent for each period. Fourth-quarter net income reached $ 248.7 million, or $ 1.71 per share, for the latest quarter from $ 219.6 million, or $ 1.51 per share, a year earlier. Revenue for the quarter rose 10.9 percent to $ 3.65 billion from $ 3.29 billion a year earlier. For the full year, profits rose to $ 822.8 million, or $ 5.66 per share, in 1988 compared with $ 724.8 million, or $ 5.02 per share, in 1987. Sales for the year rose 10.6 percent to $ 12.5 billion from $ 11.3 billion a year earlier. <ORGANIZATION> Westinghouse </ORGANIZATION> has been extracting itself from less profitable businesses by selling them or arranging mergers and joint ventures. Operating profits rose in the fourth quarter and for the year in the company's industries, electronics and broadcasting groups. Operating profits fell for the quarter and were unchanged for the year in the energy and utility group, while they fell for both the quarter and the year in the commercial group. Financial services' operating profit held steady for the year but declined significantly in the fourth quarter due primarily to increased loan charge-offs and additions to loan loss reserves.
