<HEAD>AMR Doubles Annual Earnings in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the parent of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, on Wednesday reported record net earnings for 1988 of $ 476.8 million, more than double the $ 198.4 million it earned in 1987. <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> also said its 1988 profit-sharing fund will total $ 121 million. The fund will be paid to employees in March. AMR's earnings per share for 1988 were $ 7.66, up from $ 3.28 in 1987. <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> also set a net earnings record in the fourth quarter of 1988 of $ 116.7 million, or $ 1.87 a share, compared with a 1987 fourth-quarter net loss of $ 805,000. `` Our share of domestic industry passenger miles increased by more than that of any major carrier during the year,'' said <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> Chairman and President <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Crandall </PERSON>. `` In the fourth quarter, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> carried more revenue passenger miles and provided more available seat miles than any other carrier.'' AMR's revenue for the year increased 22.6 percent to $ 8.82 billion, up from $ 7.20 billion. American's yield, or average amount of revenue per passenger mile, increased 7.7 percent from 1987, while revenue passenger miles increased 14 percent from the year before. AMR's revenue in the fourth quarter totaled $ 2.37 billion, an increase of 25.8 percent from the $ 1.88 billion in the fourth quarter of 1987. American flew a record 64.77 billion revenue passenger miles in 1988, up 14 percent from 56.79 billion flown in 1987. In the fourth quarter, <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> flew 16.71 billion revenue passenger miles, up 21.3 percent from the fourth quarter of 1987.
