<HEAD>Ameritech's Profit Up 4.1 Percent in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, citing the popularity of cellular phones and a big increase in new phone lines, on Wednesday reported a 4.1 percent rise in net income during 1988 to $ 1.24 billion. Revenue during the year increased 3.7 percent to $ 9.9 billion, the company said. `` Revenue growth reflects an increase of 375,000 <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> company customer lines, up 2.5 percent over the prior year _ the largest increase in our history,'' said <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Weiss </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> chairman and chief executive officer. <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> is the parent of <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> telephone companies serving <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>. The 1988 results also reflect growth at an <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> arm, the <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enterprise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>. The unit reported a 14 percent increase in revenue, due mostly to a 68 percent increase in cellular lines, to more than 146,000. Adjusted for a 2-for-1 stock split, <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> earnings per share in 1988 were $ 4.55, up from $ 4.24 in 1987. Net income for the fourth quarter was $ 309.7 million, down from $ 322.2 million for the same period in 1987. The company said fourth-quarter revenue was reduced by higher expenses and the absence of divested operations.
