<HEAD>Holly Farms Directors Consider Buyout Offers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Directors of <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> met late into the night in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Wednesday to consider $ 1 billion takeover bids from two rival suitors. Officials on all sides of the long-running battle for control of <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION> and leadership of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> chicken industry declined comment Wednesday. Executives of <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Omaha </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Neb. </LOCATION>, declined to say whether they raised their bid for <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION>. Rival bidders at <ORGANIZATION> Tyson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Springdale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ark. </LOCATION>, could not be reached for comment. <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION> executives said they did not expect to announce results of the meeting until this morning. If the board recommends a sale to <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION> and if shareholders go along with that recommendation, <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION> executives have said the company is expected to operate independently of the food conglomerate. If the board recommends that shareholders sell their stock to <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON>, and the shareholders follow that advice, <PERSON> Holly </PERSON> <PERSON> Farms </PERSON> will become part of the poultry empire founded by a man who ran out of gas in <LOCATION> Springdale </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ark. </LOCATION>, and started what became the country's largest chicken processor <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION> is seeking court permission to proceed with a contract reached in November to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION>.
